message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. This paper deals with language models and their knowledge, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Specifically, the paper proposes methods to improve the accuracy of extracting relational knowledge from language models, which is a common task in NLP. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
